50.261-0500"},{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/issue/31380/comment/82102","id":"82102","author":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/user?username=hspencer","name":"hspencer","key":"hspencer","accountId":"557058:4a3a93bc-21f8-4658-9f5b-9cb484c910a7","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/ea43d7b9d5b27468a749f9bd25650176?s=48&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3FownerId%3Dhspencer%26avatarId%3D10407%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","24x24":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/ea43d7b9d5b27468a749f9bd25650176?s=24&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dsmall%26ownerId%3Dhspencer%26avatarId%3D10407%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","16x16":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/ea43d7b9d5b27468a749f9bd25650176?s=16&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dxsmall%26ownerId%3Dhspencer%26avatarId%3D10407%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","32x32":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/ea43d7b9d5b27468a749f9bd25650176?s=32&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dmedium%26ownerId%3Dhspencer%26avatarId%3D10407%26noRedirect%3Dtrue"},"displayName":"Harold Spencer Jr.","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Los_Angeles"},"body":"[~vasya],\r\n\r\nVerified that this issue is fixed.  \r\n\r\nEucalyptus Version:  4.1.0-0.0.23021.351.20150116git411b4a0.el6\r\n\r\nOne thing I noticed is that if you look at the [AWS documentation regarding Block Device Mapping concepts|http://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSEC2/latest/UserGuide/block-device-mapping-concepts.html#block-device-mapping-def], they have certain device recommendations for instance store volumes and EBS volumes.  However, if you launch an instance on AWS that doesn't adhere to the recommendation (for example):\r\n{code}\r\n$ aws ec2 run-instances --key-name harold-euca --image-id ami-fae89592 --block-device-mappings \"[{\\\"DeviceName\\\":\\\"/dev/sdf\\\",\\\"Ebs\\\":{\\\"SnapshotId\\\":\\\"snap-5fb18ae9\\\"}}, {\\\"DeviceName\\\":\\\"/dev/sdg\\\",\\\"VirtualName\\\":\\\"ephemeral0\\\"}]\" --profile harold-work\r\n$ aws ec2 describe-instances --instance-ids i-cad0e431 --profile harold-workRESERVATIONS\t048212016277\tr-dba53230\r\nGROUPS\tsg-772c811f\tdefault\r\nINSTANCES\t0\tx86_64\tNone\tFalse\txen\tami-fae89592\ti-cad0e431\t m1.small\taki-919dcaf8\tharold-euca\t2015-01-17T03:38:00.000Z\tip-10-4-179-13.ec2.internal\t10.4.179.13\tec2-54-197-106-97.compute-1.amazonaws.com\t54.197.106.97\t/dev/sda1\tebs\tNone\tparavirtual\r\nBLOCKDEVICEMAPPINGS\t/dev/sda1\r\nEBS\t2015-01-17T03:38:03.000Z\tTrue\tattached\tvol-01264b4a\r\nBLOCKDEVICEMAPPINGS\t/dev/sdf\r\nEBS\t2015-01-17T03:38:03.000Z\tTrue\tattached\tvol-d6264b9d\r\nMONITORING\tdisabled\r\nPLACEMENT\tus-east-1b\tNone\tdefault\r\nSECURITYGROUPS\tsg-772c811f\tdefault\r\nSTATE\t16\trunning\r\n{code}\r\nEverything still works just fine:\r\n{code}\r\nubuntu@ip-10-4-179-13:~$ lsblk\r\nNAME  MAJ:MIN RM   SIZE RO TYPE MOUNTPOINT\r\nxvdf  202:80   0     5G  0 disk\r\nxvdg  202:96   0 149.1G  0 disk /mnt\r\nxvda1 202:1    0     8G  0 disk /\r\nxvda3 202:3    0   896M  0 disk [SWAP]\r\n{code}\r\nIn short, I think its ok that we aren't strict as to which range of block devices at used for instance store volumes and EBS volumes.  \r\n\r\nThe only issue I experienced was the lack of formatting for ephemeral devices (EUCA-10404).\r\n\r\n*Steps*\r\n\r\n# Set up a Eucalyptus 4.1.0 (4.1.0-0.0.23021.351.20150116git411b4a0.el6) cloud with VMware Broker\r\n#  Bundle, upload and register an [Ubuntu Trusty image|http://images.objectstorage.cloud.qa1.eucalyptus-systems.com:8773/trusty-server-cloudimg-amd64-disk1-20150115.img].  For example:\r\n{code}\r\n# euca-install-image -b ubuntu-trusty-server-amd64-20150116 -n ubuntu-trusty-amd64 -r x86_64 -i /mnt/ephemeral/trusty-server-cloudimg-amd64-disk1-20150115.img --region admin-account2@vmware --virtualization-type hvm\r\n{code}\r\n{code}\r\n# euca-describe-images --region admin-account2@vmware\r\nIMAGE\temi-df999b8b\tubuntu-trusty-server-amd64-20150116/trusty-server-cloudimg-amd64-disk1-20150115.img.manifest.xml\t881029380924\tavailable\tprivate\tx86_64\tmachine\t\t\t\tinstance-store\thvm\r\n{code}\r\n# Launch an instance from the EMI\r\n{code}\r\n# euca-run-instances -k admin-account2 -t m1.xlarge emi-df999b8b --region admin-account2@vmware\r\n{code}\r\n# Followed the steps in the [KB article that explains how to create an EBS-backed EMI from an running Instance Store-Backed instance|https://support.eucalyptus.com/hc/en-us/articles/201605884-Creating-an-Ubuntu-EBS-backed-EMI-from-an-Existing-Instance-Store-Backed-Instance].\r\n# Created another volume and snapshot of that volume:\r\n{code}\r\n# euca-create-volume -s 7 -z one --region admin-account2@vmware\r\nVOLUME\tvol-1b74368c\t7\t\tone\tcreating\t2015-01-17T05:00:58.882Z\r\n# euca-describe-volumes --region admin-account2@vmware\r\nVOLUME\tvol-1b74368c\t7\t\tone\tavailable\t2015-01-17T05:00:58.882Z\tstandard\r\n# euca-create-snapshot vol-1b74368c --region admin-account2@vmware\r\nSNAPSHOT\tsnap-37bc411c\tvol-1b74368c\tpending\t2015-01-17T05:01:58.356Z\t881029380924\t7\r\n# euca-describe-snapshots --region admin-account2@vmware\r\nSNAPSHOT\tsnap-37bc411c\tvol-1b74368c\tcompleted\t2015-01-17T05:01:58.356Z\t100%\t881029380924\t7\r\n{code}\r\n# Launched instance from EBS-backed EMI defining ephemeral storage (instance store volume) and EBS volume\r\n{code}\r\n# euca-describe-images --region admin-account2@vmware\r\nIMAGE\temi-dd4f2c1e\t881029380924/ubuntu-trusty-x86-64-ebs-hvm\t881029380924\tavailable\tprivate\tx86_64\tmachine\t\t\t\tebs\thvm\r\nBLOCKDEVICEMAPPING\tEBS\t/dev/sda\tsnap-51030421\t10\ttrue\tstandard\r\n\r\n# euca-run-instances -k admin-account2 emi-dd4f2c1e -t m1.large -b /dev/sdc=ephemeral0 -b /dev/sdf=snap-37bc411c --region admin-account2@vmware\r\nRESERVATION\tr-f29abbc2\t881029380924\tdefault\r\nINSTANCE\ti-ceeed49e\temi-dd4f2c1e\t0.0.0.0\t0.0.0.0\tpending\tadmin-account2\t0\t\tm1.large\t2015-01-17T05:20:02.384Z\tone\t\t\t\tmonitoring-disabled\t0.0.0.0\t0.0.0.0\t\t\tebs\t\t\t\t\thvm\t\t\tsg-e35bf931\r\n\r\n# euca-describe-instances i-ceeed49e --region admin-account2@vmware\r\nRESERVATION\tr-f29abbc2\t881029380924\tdefault\r\nINSTANCE\ti-ceeed49e\temi-dd4f2c1e\t10.111.30.148\t172.16.51.185\trunning\tadmin-account2\t0\t\tm1.large\t2015-01-17T05:20:02.384Z\tone\t\t\t\tmonitoring-disabled\t10.111.30.148\t172.16.51.185\t\t\tebs\t\t\t\t\thvm\t\t\tsg-e35bf931\t\t\t\tx86_64\r\nBLOCKDEVICE\t/dev/sdf\tvol-aab10b7c\t2015-01-17T05:20:02.502Z\ttrue\r\nBLOCKDEVICE\t/dev/sda\tvol-db971aef\t2015-01-17T05:20:02.577Z\ttrue\r\n{code}\r\n# SSH'd into instance and confirmed that both devices were present.  Also checked to make sure ephemeral was correct size based upon instance type used.\r\n{code}\r\n# euca-describe-instance-types --show-capacity --region admin-account2@vmware m1.large\r\nINSTANCETYPE\tName      CPUs  Memory (MiB)  Disk (GiB)  Used / Total  Used %\r\nINSTANCETYPE\tm1.large     2           512          10     2 /     2    100%\r\n\r\n## ephemeral should be 10 gigs ##\r\n\r\n# ssh -i admin-account2 ubuntu@10.111.30.148\r\nubuntu@ip-172-16-51-185:~$ lsblk\r\nNAME   MAJ:MIN RM SIZE RO TYPE MOUNTPOINT\r\nsda      8:0    0  10G  0 disk\r\n└─sda1   8:1    0  10G  0 part /\r\nsdb      8:16   0   7G  0 disk\r\nsdc      8:32   0  10G  0 disk\r\n\r\n## Confirmed EUCA-10401 was still an issue for EBS-backed instance ##\r\nubuntu@ip-172-16-51-185:~$ sudo parted /dev/sdc print\r\nsudo: unable to resolve host ip-172-16-51-185\r\nError: /dev/sdc: unrecognised disk label\r\n\r\n## EBS volume created correctly ##\r\n\r\nubuntu@ip-172-16-51-185:~$ sudo parted /dev/sdb print\r\nsudo: unable to resolve host ip-172-16-51-185\r\nError: /dev/sdb: unrecognised disk label\r\n{code}","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/user?username=hspencer","name":"hspencer","key":"hspencer","accountId":"557058:4a3a93bc-21f8-4658-9f5b-9cb484c910a7","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/ea43d7b9d5b27468a749f9bd25650176?s=48&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3FownerId%3Dhspencer%26avatarId%3D10407%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","24x24":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/ea43d7b9d5b27468a749f9bd25650176?s=24&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dsmall%26ownerId%3Dhspencer%26avatarId%3D10407%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","16x16":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/ea43d7b9d5b27468a749f9bd25650176?s=16&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dxsmall%26ownerId%3Dhspencer%26avatarId%3D10407%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","32x32":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/ea43d7b9d5b27468a749f9bd25650176?s=32&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dmedium%26ownerId%3Dhspencer%26avatarId%3D10407%26noRedirect%3Dtrue"},"displayName":"Harold Spencer Jr.","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Los_Angeles"},"created":"2015-01-16T23:48:07.175-0600","updated":"2015-01-16T23:48:07.175-0600"}],"maxResults":4,"total":4,"startAt":0},"customfield_11808":null,"worklog":{"startAt":0,"maxResults":20,"total":0,"worklogs":[]}}}